cafes.name: Naughty Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 3742 Tennessee Ave Suite 100, Chattanooga, TN 37409, USA

text.text:
What a wonderful experience !! They had approximately 40 cats in a couple of rooms. One room nicely decorated with couches and chairs and cat furniture. This room is a little dark on purpose. Fun to sit and let the cats come to you. There is a second room with full light and also lots of seating areas for cats and humans . Very clean! Amazingly friendly staff.
There are binders with all the cat information in case you like to adopt one.
Highly recommended activity to have fun and support a good cause!

We had never experienced a cat cafe before and I hope they are all as well done at the Naughty Cat Cafe! Several rooms full of cats to love on! Even a quiet room for the new residents to get used to their new lodgings. Highly recommend if you love cats. You will want to take them all home!

They have so many cats right now (12/13/2024)! All of them have so much personality and they’re sooooo soft! I came here with friends as a birthday gift to myself, I’m so glad I did. It is very calming sitting with the cats! They dim the lights and play soothing music while the cats just roam around. It is also extremely clean and the restroom smells great as well! They do provide binders all around the sitting area so you can learn about each cat, along with how to adopt one if you fall in love with one of the fur babies! As well as the cat petting, they provide you one free drink — whether that be hot coffee, hot tea, soda, chocolate milk, or cold water! They also sell reasonably priced products, such as jewelry, cat toys, shot glasses, little pastries, and they even have cans of alcohol for sale (if that’s your thing!). I would 100% recommend this lovely place to anybody who even remotely enjoys cats! There are many different areas to sit, their one rule is to never pick up any of the cats.

cafes.name: Catfeine Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 517 Cason Ln D, Murfreesboro, TN 37128, USA

text.text: This place was a really sweet experience and IMMACULATE to boot. I wasn't sure what to expect but its such a humane way to provide an opportunity for cats to be fostered/adopted. The owner Taura is very kind and is very involved in the process and makes sure the cats are cared for. I have NEVER been in a cleaner environment with that many animals, anywhere!! The vibe was laid back, comfortable and you would not know there were 20 cats there. You could tell they were comfortable and cared for in that environment. Those cats aren't just fosters to that business, they're family. I would give more stars if I could!!!!!
Absolutely love this place, the environment was very friendly, the staff was super welcoming and the cats well they were really energetic today lol. Took some silly photos of the cats

You have cat to be kitten me right meow!!! This place is everything a cat and coffee lover wants. The cats here are all so sweet and well taken care of. I set up my laptop and worked for a couple hours while the kitties played around me. I wish I could adopt them all!!!

cafes.name: Cleo's Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 134 Bus Terminal Rd, Oak Ridge, TN 37830, USA

text.text: I absolutely loved coming here! The cats were all well taken care of, and they all seemed comfortable. I wish I could take them all home! The woman working was really nice and their customer service is on par! I would definitely recommend it and I'll be back!

A coworker and I have relocated over to Cleo’s a couple of times and it is so awesome to sit and work with a kitty by your side. Our first time, one sat next to my laptop and just watched me type. All of the cats are so loving and sweet! The cafe is clean and well taken care of. Their coffee was fantastic too! I had a s’mores latte that was delicious. I will absolutely be going back again and again. I wish they would add a membership for a monthly fee that would cover a number of visits :)

We enjoyed our time here!! All cats were so cute! Some of them were very friendly and playful, some were more cautions - they were probably new ones, but they will get used to the environment. Those cautions ones were also so incredibly cute. They are all for adoption too.

The place is clean and friendly, nice coffee, we’ll certainly come back here!

If you are considering to get a pet, cats are an awesome choice. We have four cats that we adopted just from the streets, three of them were already adults, one was a 2 months old kitten. They bring us a lot of joy.

cafes.name: The Catio Cat Lounge
cafes.address: 2416 Music Valley Dr Suite 119, Nashville, TN 37214, USA

text.text: My family went to the cat lounge on Saturday and had the best time. The staff were friendly and we loved having time to visit with all of the cats. We had plenty of time to take pictures and pet several cats. Some cats even wanted to play with the toys. We got lots of cat snuggles and will definitely visit again the next time we are in Nashville! I definitely recommend visiting this cat lounge.

So many cute kitties. They are well taken for and have so many toys and places to chill. The staff is friendly and compassionate. I was glad to see my fellow patrons were kind and respectful of the cats' spaces. Please donate to this place if you can. And adopt if possible.

This has been one of the best Cat Cafe / Cat Lounges I’ve visited. While traveling I always try to seek out new cat cafes… and I’m really glad I found this one. The place is massive, and they had a bunch of really sweet cats. In addition o kittens and younger cats, they also had a “senior” and special needs cat room. All of it is very well done, and the cats all appear very happy. While there I didn’t buy any of their packaged snacks or drinks, but I did buy a ton of their awesome branded merch. Really great place to relax!

cafes.name: The Senior Catio
cafes.address: 2416 Music Valley Dr Suite 119, Nashville, TN 37214, USA

text.text: This is such a beautiful, calming, therapeutic place to hang out and the people who work there are so kind and sweet (specially the lady with glasses who received me and my boyfriend on my first visit and explained me how this cat lounge experience works). I couldn't contain my happiness being surrounded by so many beautiful cats walking around. I went with my boyfriend and we had a blast! They also have tons of toys for you to play with the cats and lots of couches and areas to just sit and play. This is such a great and cute place to go with the family, on my next trip to Tennessee this will definitely be one of my first places to visit!

Today was my first visit (of many more to come!) to the Senior Catio. It is a lovely and peaceful place to meet the sweetest cats! I definitely recommend it if you are looking for a cat to adopt or just need to de-stress. There are lots of snacks and merch available for purchase.

The Senior Catio is a must-do experience for any cat lover. The Senior Catio is the sister location to the well-loved Catio Cat Lounge and is focused on the well-being and placement of senior cats. This environment is perfect for the older cats and allows them to flourish in a comfortable and safe environment. We spent an hour amongst the cats and had a wonderful experience. I highly recommend taking the trip out to see and/or adopt one of these wonderful cats. We miss them already. ❤️🐈

My experience was so great! These kitties are all very well taken care of and they're all up for adoption. You can get a bite to eat and drink and hang out with these cute kitties by the hour. There is plenty of room to sit and chill, have some fun playing with kitties, and getting some much needed kitty time in if you're away from home. The staff is very friendly and you can just tell that they love what they do. Very much recommend!

I recently visited Scruffy’s Cafe and it was an amazing experience from start to finish! The cafe offers a cozy and welcoming atmosphere where you can enjoy delicious lattes while spending time with some incredibly friendly and well-cared-for cats. The cats are all available for adoption, and you can tell they are loved and treated with the utmost care by the staff. The staff themselves were wonderful—knowledgeable, kind, and always happy to share a bit of info about the cats and their personalities. Whether you're looking to adopt or just unwind with some cute cats, I highly recommend this place.

This cat café is adorable! The atmosphere here is so chill and you can tell all of the kitties are well taken care of. Had a wonderful time playing with and petting the kitties. I also tried a hot chocolate and cake pop while here and it was super yummy. I would definitely recommend this place if you like cats and chill vibes.

Compared to the rest of the zoo, the cafeteria has a little that could be improved on. Mainly, ok solely, the food.

It’s quick to order because there are several kiosks to order from. Food is expensive as it usually is at a zoo. Burger was bleh. I didn’t eat it all. It was gross actually lol! I enjoyed the free refill zoo cup though!
Food was cold. Cheese on hamburger didn't even melt. Fries would have been good if not cold.

The line went fairly quick and the food was actually pretty good! We got burgers and fries. You can sit and watch the monkeys while you eat altho not sure that's a good idea 🤣. Overall a pretty reasonable priced good place to grab a bite to eat while visiting the zoo.

I've become a regular to this coffee shop over the last year, and I'm never disappointed in its service, environment, and drinks! The staff are very nice and show how much they care about their customers and the service they provide. As a college student, it is perfect for me to go here and knock out some studying for a few hours in a day. They are very involved in the community as well, holding events consistently throughout each month. I would easily recommend this place to anyone.

An AMAZING addition to selmer , it’s like our own Starbucks but with that cozy home feel, the Barista even brought me the drink as I was on the sofa.

Adorable cat themed, 100% will be a returning customer. And recommend to everyone

This coffee shop is absolutely adorable, tons of room and space to do your work in privacy. The theme is cats and I just love how they brought everything together and made it one beautiful place with great Coffee, delicious snacks, and the perfect atmosphere.
The workers are very nice, knowledgeable and personable. Definitely give this coffee shop a try.

cafes.name: The Phat Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 515 E Church St, Greeneville, TN 37743, USA

text.text: Delicious food. Great service. Would definitely recommend eating lunch here. My friend and I both had the club sandwich. It was loaded with plenty of meat. It was really good. I had loaded potato soup and it was delicious. My friend really liked her tomato soup. My husband had taco salad. It is huge. He loved it. French fries are to die for. So glad I picked this restaurant. Thank you for the wonderful food.
Their food was absolutely amazing, it was probably the best salad i’ve ever had. My only problem is their hours! I wish they closed later than 2:30 so I could go there more often.

This was our first time eating here and we was amazed at how good the food was! I tried the club sandwich and it was with out a doubt the best I've ever had! The cheeseburger is fresh patted out meat and was awesome too. The fries are hand cut and amazing. The owner is very nice and friendly and makes sure everything is just right and makes you feel welcomed. The inside of this place is very nice and cozy with real hard wood floors that has a very nice cozy feeling. I HIGHLY recommend eating here. As for us it won't be our last time coming here to eat!

Visited at 11:30am, because we arrived downtown thirty minutes before our appointment and needed a place to appreciate Life and Living. The Heart warming energy of the resident Cats is wonderful. Highly recommended, bring a partner, friend, date. If you really Love cats, get closer right here.

I have just moved out to Asheville, walking around the area I wasn't looking for a cat cafe, but the second I saw it I knew I had to check it out. First the aesthetic of this Cafe is amazing, beautiful design that makes it feel like it was made for the cats, and for the people of Asheville. The employees were very friendly and helpful when it came to understanding how the cafe worked and what all can be done here. I grabbed a drink, which regrettably I don't remember the name of as it was a long day, and throughly enjoy it! Once I got to hang out with the cats I felt such joy, not being able to have a cat at the moment this was the perfect opportunity to experience being around them again. All of them were very sweet and the kittens were adorable to see and play with. I will be coming back here to enjoy the Cafe and experience they offer!

What a cute and cute wonderful place! Offers coffee, tea, beers, wine, while you play with kitties. Adorably decorated and VERY clean - no kitty smell at all! $12pp for 30 min got you access to 2 rooms. One with older cats and one for kittens. Buy a tube of treats for $1 and you’ll get lots of attention! Kitties are for adoption and they seem to have helped over 150 cats get homes since the start of the year. This is my new retirement plan LOL

Lenoir.name: Brews and Mews Cat Cafe
Lenoir.address: 219 N Main St, Lenoir, NC 28645, USA

text.text: Came for a friend's birthday with high expectations and was not disappointed. The Moon boba tea was delicious, and the cats made my heart melt. The cat area was a little dirty, but the rest of the cafe had a chill atmosphere that made me feel right at home. Will definitely be coming back the next time I'm in the area!

wanted to say today was such a wonderful experience! my partner and i had a great time during our 3PM appointment, and during our appointment they introduced a new cat to the room. as someone who has worked in cat cafes in the past, they are doing top tier work to take care of these cats. the cats are very sweet, very social, and i can tell the staff goes to great efforts to make all of this happen. every drink i’ve gotten from here has been amazing as well, and i see why people stop in just for the drinks all the time! definitely support this business, whether it’s booking an appointment or just getting a sweet drink!

Great coffee and boba drinks and fun to watch and play with the cats. Definitely stop for drinks even if you don't like cats. You can just watch them if you don't want to play. The holiday decorations are lovely and the staff are great fun.

cafes.name: Goodies Bar & Grill
cafes.address: 673 Inman St E, Cleveland, TN 37311, USA

text.text: Guys, please open during the week day it’s not good to close 3 days. What about to open Tuesday and Wednesday so you can close Monday?
It was definitely a grown and sexy vibe. Liquor flowing hookah blowing 💪🏾
Nice place to have drinks and listen to music

cafes.name: Alley Cat's Cafe
cafes.address: 224 N Maple St, Adamsville, TN 38310, USA

text.text: Love the food and the staff! Great atmosphere
Nice quiet place to eat.  Friendly service and food cooked right.
You come here you have to have the LOADED BAKE POTATO, very unique and good

Great coffee spot!! building is actually red, not blue as on older pictures. drive through works great, you can stop on either side and order from a large menu of items. we went with classic lattes, regular milk 🥛 it tasted great! i love my coffee strong, so would take an extra shot of espresso next time! overall great experience and friendly service! nice people working in here!

Their prices are good. I got a caramel frappe and a cream cheese danish. I really wanted to love this place since it's a small business and there aren't many places to get coffee nearby. The Danish was good but the frappe was not. I was disappointed. I drank half of it and was left with just a big pile of weird flavorless sno-cone-like ice filling half the cup. I've never had a frappe separate and be like that before. It didn't stay blended somehow and my drink just didn't taste that good. Maybe it was just that particular drink. I might go back one more time and just try their iced coffee instead.
If I do, I will adjust my review.
Pretty cute drive thru coffee booth. Latte is good, if you like your coffee strong then an extra shot will not hurt. Overall very fast and friendly service.
